  "categories": [
    {
      "title": "ElizaOS Discord Community Activity - May 14, 2026",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "In the general discussion channel, Shaw mentioned that the current setup uses Qwen with some optimizations, and that a fine-tuning pipeline is being developed to improve model performance for calling actions and planning. The channel also saw several users posting self-promotional messages, including one user advertising AI and full-stack development services, and another posting a spam investment solicitation that was warned by a moderator (Odilitime) with a threat of a ban if repeated. A job posting was shared by Sindy seeking testers at 35 per hour, moderators at 450 per week, and a Solidity developer at negotiable pay for an onchain game team, described as remote and flexible.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1778810281581-ct8spq.jpg"
        },
        {
          "text": "In the coders channel, ReaWorks shared a project called the Pay or Burn escrow protocol deployed on Base Mainnet, designed specifically for autonomous AI agents. The protocol uses a game-theoretic mechanism where if two agents cannot agree on a task outcome, the escrowed funds are burned, eliminating incentives for malicious behavior. Key architectural choices include 100 percent pull-payment to avoid issues with reverting receiver contracts, no user interface with only a raw smart contract and SDKs in Python and C++, and a burn logic that destroys expected value for bad actors. The project is available on GitHub. Separately, Xavier raised a question about excessive Neynar credit consumption, noting his agent was using around 300 credits per hour on Farcaster notifications instead of the expected 4, and Odilitime suggested that using webhooks could reduce consumption. The coders channel also received the same spam investment message and a self-promotional post from an AI and ML engineer seeking work on LLM systems and agent workflows.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1300025221834739744",
          "images": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/ai-agent-escrow-protocol_c29e9973.jpg"
        }
      ],
